value.value: The most apical pseudopodomere of the tarsus, delimited by a membrane in place of the foot slit suture. The membrane extends from each side to meet dorsally and thus forms an additional joint. Only some araneomorph spiders such as several Synspermiata or palpimanoids have an articulate podotarsite.
A hook-shaped sclerotized structure arising from the leg or palpal pretarsus.
Each of the paired leg tarsal claws.
The prolateral superior claw.
The retrolateral superior claw.
The median, unpaired claw located apically on the leg pretarsus.
An eye where the retina receives the light directly, as opposed to being reflected by a tapetum.
The lens of the anterior median eye.
The lens of the anterior lateral eye.
The lens of the posterior lateral eye.
The lens of the posterior lateral eye.
A medium-sized seta with curved shaft, usually with barbs, inervated by three neurons. This is the most frequent and widespread kind of seta.

A seta with a small socket, bent in angle immediately after its insertion, so that it lies parallel to the cuticular surface. Scales lack innervation. They can have a wide variety of shapes, including feathery, cylindrical, and flat.
A cusple on the labium of some Mygalomorphae.
A silk fiber produced through an aciniform gland spigot.
A silk fiber produced through a major ampullate gland spigot.
A silk fiber produced through a minor ampullate gland spigot.
A silk fiber produced through a paracribellar gland spigot.
A silk fiber produced through a modified gland spigot.
A silk fiber produced through a cylindrical gland spigot.
A silk fiber with glue coating produced through a piriform gland spigot.
A silk fiber produced through a cribellar gland spigot.
A modified gland spigot in araneoids.
A modified gland spigot in deinopoids.
The base of the flagelliform gland spigot.
The shaft of the flagelliform gland spigot.
The base of the pseudoflagelliform gland spigot.
The shaft of the pseudoflagelliform gland spigot.
The opisthosomal segment between carapace and epigastrium.
The opisthosomal segment between the pedicel and the epigastric furrow.
The opisthosomal segment between the epigastric furrow and the spinnerets.
The opisthosomal segment bearing the anterior spinnerets.
The opisthosomal segment bearing the posterior spinnerets.
The external opening leading to the booklung atrium.
The atrium of the posterior booklung.
The atrium of the anterior booklung.
A tracheal structure with tubular shape.
The opening of a trachea to the exterior.
A ventral paired apodeme on the posterior end of the opisthosomal segment.
A tracheal tube arising from the interpulmonary fold in the 2nd segment.
The 8th, most distal article of the leg, articulated with the tarsus and bearing the claws.
Segment on the leg, connected to other articles or to prosoma by articulate joints.
The pretarsus of leg 1.
The pretarsus of leg 2.
The pretarsus of leg 3.
The pretarsus of leg 4.
Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.
A small sclerite on the fang articulation, where the fang flexor tendon inserts.
The shaft of the claw tuft seta.
The socket of the claw tuft seta.
